## 10. README Framing (draft)

```
PriorAI — Multimodal Prior Authorization Agent

A locally-runnable AI agent that automates prior authorization package
assembly for outpatient clinics. Given a patient ID, an optional clinical
PDF, and an optional clinician voice note, PriorAI queries a FHIR R4
server, validates diagnosis codes, checks medical necessity criteria,
runs a CatBoost denial risk model, and generates a structured authorization
submission and draft appeal letter.

Stack: Claude API (tool-use) · HAPI FHIR R4 · Synthea · CatBoost ·
faster-whisper · FastAPI · React

Data: HAPI FHIR R4 server populated with Synthea synthetic patients.
No real patient data is used. Epic sandbox integration is in progress.

Setup (3 commands):
  docker compose up -d        # starts HAPI FHIR + backend
  python load_synthea.py      # loads synthetic patients
  npm run dev                 # starts frontend at localhost:5173

Set CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5 for development,
claude-sonnet-4-5 for demo-quality letter output.
```

